# Starkzap Product Rules

- Use Starkzap staking conventions as source of truth for UX and method naming:
  - `wallet.stake(pool, amount)` for smart enter/add.
  - `wallet.claimPoolRewards(pool)` for claims.
  - `wallet.exitPoolIntent(pool, amount)` then `wallet.exitPool(pool)` for unstake completion.
- Favor discovery over hardcoding:
  - Resolve pools with `getStakerPools(...)` and token symbol matching.
  - Only override `staking.contract` when explicitly needed.
- Wallet UX expectations:
  - Keep Cartridge-based flow smooth and non-blocking.
  - Surface actionable errors (`Pool not found`, `No claimable rewards`, cooldown pending).
- State visibility requirements in wallet UI:
  - Show staked, rewards, total, unpooling, and exit time when available.
  - Explain unstake as a two-step process in plain language.
- For any staking action:
  - show immediate feedback (button busy text),
  - show pending confirmation toast,
  - refresh wallet state after transaction confirmation.
- Reference docs for accuracy:
  - `https://docs.starkzap.com/llms-full.txt`
  - `https://docs.starknet.io/build/starkzap/staking`
  - `docs/STARKNET_DOCS_INDEX.md`
